`NewSyncMap` was renamed to `MakeSyncMap`. This is a potentially breaking API change for any internal/external call sites still using `NewSyncMap`. If this is intentional, ensure all references are updated; otherwise consider keeping a backward-compatible wrapper:

```go
func NewSyncMap[T any]() *SyncMap[T] { return MakeSyncMap[T]() }
```

This avoids build failures and eases migration.

```suggestion
func MakeSyncMap[T any]() *SyncMap[T] {
	return &SyncMap[T]{
		lock: &sync.Mutex{},
		m:    make(map[string]T),
	}
}

